I wake up to the sounds of an alarm screeching in the town center. A weird pit fell into my stomach, as though someone had knocked the
wind out of me. I knew what today was, I wanted to think my mind was wandering in a dream land, a utopia, but I was wrong. This was reality.
I walk out of my room, and see my mother cooking on the kitchen stove, the aroma of cinnamon, and apple filling up the room. She sobbed
silently to herself, as she too knew what the day was. cheeks. "Mom, it will be ok, I most likely won't even be selected to fight in the games today."
